OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,407,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1783711192
OL,3,CCouncil narrowly votes to keep
OL,4,Ccontroversial traffic control scheme
OL,6,FCllr Ed Plowden said: "We hear the
OL,7,Fvoices of people who have found the
OL,8,FEBLN trial challenging" but added that
OL,9,Fmaking the scheme permanent would
OL,10,Fbring "positive changes to travel
OL,11,Fbehaviour, improve air quality and
OL,12,Froad safety, making sure the benefits
OL,13,Fof a Liveable Neighbourhood are widely
OL,14,Ffelt by residents."
OL,16,FSome residents claim there is an
OL,17,Falleged lack of consultation from the
OL,18,Fruling Green Party.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
